text: Harrisonburg is a city in Rockingham County, Virginia. It had 51,814 people at the 2020 census. Harrisonburg is the county seat of Rockingham County. Harrisonburg is home to James Madison University and Eastern Mennonite University. == References == == Other websites == * Harrisonburg Tourism * City of Harrisonburg * Harrisonburg-Rockingham Chamber of Commerce * Harrisonburg City Public Schools * Daily News Record (Newspaper) * WHSV - TV 3 * Rocktown Weekly (Alternative Newspaper owned by the DNR) * Virginia Quilt Museum Category:Cities in Virginia Category:County seats in Virginia Category:1730s establishments in Virginia Category:1737 establishments
